The commercial book, as you've heard already now from John a couple of times, basically right on baseline, maybe a hair above but right there. And then the two government books of business, a few percentage points below. So I won't go further than that. But maybe John, you could give some insight into how you're seeing things within the next six months.

John Rex -- Chief Financial Officer

Good morning, Ralph. So yes, so you blend a little bit, just a little bit below overall, right, when you blend the books and you weight our books across in terms of what we are seeing in the second quarter. And then as you might expect, that trends up progressively every quarter. Every quarter, you'd see rising in that overall level of utilization and the expectations as we head into the end of the year.

Embedded in that is also a view in terms of what happens with intensity, acuity levels. One comment that -- a question that we've often received is what are we seeing currently in acuity levels to progress. And part of the impact as we progress in the second half is an expectation that you do see rising acuity levels. I'd tell you, we haven't observed that yet.

But it's still probably a little bit early to say. When we -- among the things we look at, we look at new cancer diagnoses, new cardiac diagnoses. Those are still running below baseline levels that we'd expect. But they're -- a view to that could continue to progress as we get into the back half of the year.

The other element in terms of just thinking about utilization and rising in the back of the year is -- and then ultimately, this is one of the -- what occurs with COVID testing and treatment costs. Clearly, there's been the evidence of the new variants and their impact in other countries and then also moving into the U.S. And even in our own data, we can see that but I would tell you still fairly limited in terms of impact. And as I sit here and look at the number of members -- of our members that we have in -- receiving treatment today in hospital beds today as we sit here this morning, still well below the levels even we sit here in mid-July, what we were seeing in the April levels.

But that could be a trend back factor also in the second half of the year as we see that progression. Thank you.

Andrew Witty -- Chief Executive Officer

